  <brief_title>Safety and Efficacy of Mobic Inj. (Meloxicam) for the Patients With OA or RA: Observational Study</brief_title>
  <official_title>Post Marketing Surveillance to Assess the Safety and Efficacy of Mobic速 (Meloxicam) Intramuscular Injection (7.5mg ~ 15mg, q.d.) up to 3 Days (in Case of Need for Prolonged Treatment, Switch to Mobic速 Capsule Therapy Was Possible) in Korean Patients With Osteoarthritis and Rheumatoid Arthritis (KFDA Regulatory Requirement PMS)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Boehringer Ingelheim</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Boehringer Ingelheim</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objective of this PMS study was to monitor and assess the safety of Mobic速
      intramuscular injection (7.5mg ~ 15mg, q.d.) up to 3 days (in case of need for prolonged
      treatment, switch to Mobic速 capsule therapy was possible) in Korean patients with
      osteoarthritis and rheumatoid arthritis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
